## Accessibility Requirements

### Compliance Target

**Standard:** WCAG 2.1 AA compliance with specific attention to dark theme accessibility and financial application requirements

### Key Requirements

**Visual:**
- Color contrast ratios: Minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text (18pt+) against dark backgrounds
- Focus indicators: 2px solid outline with 2px offset, using accent color (#0070f3) with sufficient contrast
- Text sizing: Support up to 200% zoom without horizontal scrolling, minimum 16px base font size

**Interaction:**
- Keyboard navigation: Full tab order coverage, logical focus flow, no keyboard traps, skip links for main content
- Screen reader support: Semantic HTML5, ARIA labels for complex components, live regions for real-time updates (PXL rates, tier progression)
- Touch targets: Minimum 44px × 44px interactive areas, adequate spacing between clickable elements

**Content:**
- Alternative text: Descriptive alt text for all images, tier badges, charts, and giftcard visuals
- Heading structure: Logical H1-H6 hierarchy, unique page titles, descriptive section headings
- Form labels: Explicit labels for all inputs, error messages associated with fields, clear validation feedback

**Financial Application Specific:**
- Currency announcements: Screen readers announce currency values with proper context
- Tier status: Clear announcement of tier changes and benefit updates
- Transaction confirmations: Accessible confirmation messages for all financial actions
- Error handling: Clear, actionable error messages for payment failures and validation issues

### Testing Strategy

**Automated Testing:**
- axe-core integration in CI/CD pipeline
- Lighthouse accessibility audits on all major screens
- Color contrast validation for all tier color combinations

**Manual Testing:**
- Keyboard-only navigation testing across all user flows
